                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/25073: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-09T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1921—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. With reference to the communication to which you refer in your telegram no.
                    154, of July 8, 12 noon, you may make informal reply by stating gist of
                    Department’s telegram no. 101, of July 8th, 1921. You will omit, however, any
                    reference to reports emanating from consulate at Tampico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
